15
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:41,640
I never intended for Jiali
to repay this money.

16
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,710
You didn't want her to repay it,

17
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:47,070
why did you ask her to write an IOU?

18
00:01:47,070 --> 00:01:49,120
Isn't that embarrassing Jiali?

19
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,070
Back then,

20
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:52,760
when they disagreed us to get married,

21
00:01:53,030 --> 00:01:54,230
wasn't that embarrassing?

22
00:01:55,290 --> 00:01:57,590
People need dignity.

23
00:01:58,810 --> 00:02:01,280
I don't value money that much.

24
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:04,180
But since the money is in my hands,

25
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:06,180
it has to follow my rules.

26
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:08,980
In my world, I am the boss.

27
00:02:09,380 --> 00:02:10,220
Is that wrong?

28
00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:13,780
No. You are the boss.

29
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:23,100
(IOU)

30
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:28,540
When Xiaonian returns,

31
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:31,460
this money will be given to him as a gift.

32
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:36,180
Alright.

33
00:02:39,020 --> 00:02:40,620
What kind of business
does Jiali want to do?

34
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:43,180
Didn't I tell you? Old profession.

35
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:44,180
Selling vegetables?

36
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,220
What's wrong with it?

37
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:46,180
It's nothing ashamed.

38
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:54,140
Everyone's living their lives.

39
00:03:04,260 --> 00:03:07,260
You come so early to buy vegetables.

40
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:08,780
Look, it's not even dawn yet.

41
00:03:08,820 --> 00:03:11,380
I can pick the best vegetables now.

42
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:14,180
If I come late, only the leftovers are left.

43
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:18,780
If you're not fully awake,

44
00:03:18,820 --> 00:03:20,060
why don't you go back to sleep?

45
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,580
You should have said so earlier.

46
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:22,980
I'm already here.

47
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:25,580
When you were in the army,

48
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,580
didn't you get up
even earlier for training?

49
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:30,140
I'm just worried about you.

50
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:31,380
From now on,

51
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,860
you have to get up this early every day.

52
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:34,420
I don't mind.

53
00:03:34,580 --> 00:03:35,940
I'll get used to it.

54
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:44,540
If you haven't woken up yet,

55
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,380
can you calculate the accounts correctly?

56
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:47,620
You are not good at math.

57
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:51,300
It's a small business,

58
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:53,380
it's a piece of cake for me.

59
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:55,340
Ok. Alright.

60
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:58,980
Let's go to the Bank today

61
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:00,740
and withdraw the money
to return to Jiayi.

62
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:02,380
Isn't it almost due?

63
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:03,580
If we withdraw it now,

64
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,580
we'll lose the interest.

65
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:05,980
Forget it. Let's return it to her.

66
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:07,860
It makes me feel at ease.

67
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:10,380
It seems you are quite confident.

68
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:11,580
Of course.

69
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:14,140
Alright. I'll wait for you
to make big money.

70
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:17,060
How can this make big money?

71
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:18,180
Hold on tight.

72
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:23,140
Carrot, potato, spinach

73
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:24,380
on sale. Ms.,

74
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:25,800
which vegetable do you want?

75
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:28,260
Radish and celery,

76
00:04:28,260 --> 00:04:30,660
fresh vegetables on sale!

77
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:33,020
Girl,

78
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:34,340
how much is your spinach?

79
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:35,180
Fifty cents per jin.

80
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:36,220
Fifty cents?

81
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:38,580
Others are selling it at forty-five cents.

82
00:04:38,580 --> 00:04:39,580
You want fifty cents?

83
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:40,620
Not all vegetables are the same.

84
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,100
Look at my spinach.

85
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:43,180
Let me see what's different.

86
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:44,020
It's very fresh.

87
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:45,620
Too small.

88
00:04:45,620 --> 00:04:47,220
The cheaper ones are too old to eat.

89
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:48,900
- It's too small.
- It's fresh and tasty.

90
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,460
- I won't buy it.
- Come on, buy some.

91
00:04:50,460 --> 00:04:52,420
- No, no.
- It's Fresh.

92
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:55,620
Give me one cabbage.

93
00:04:56,060 --> 00:04:57,620
Carrot, potato, spinach.

94
00:04:58,820 --> 00:05:00,060
Buy some?

95
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:50,100
Well,

96
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:52,580
about moving back,

97
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:55,620
you'd better discuss it
with Mom and Grandma.

98
00:05:55,620 --> 00:05:58,140
Yes, I was just about to say that.

99
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:00,220
Come, let me have a sip.

100
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:01,580
Be careful, it's hot.

101
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:07,020
Do you think Mom will agree?

102
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,540
Why would she disagree?

103
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,300
This is the only solution.

104
00:06:11,740 --> 00:06:13,140
To sell vegetables at Longhu Market,

105
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:16,020
I have to get up at four in the morning.

106
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:19,460
It is the closest to there.

107
00:06:19,660 --> 00:06:20,900
Besides, if I go back,

108
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:22,900
I will pay the meal fee.

109
00:06:22,980 --> 00:06:24,460
That is a must.

110
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:27,340
I have made up my mind.

111
00:06:27,940 --> 00:06:29,140
Love the job you do.

112
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:31,100
Since I've decided,

113
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:33,140
I must do this thing well.

114
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:35,860
You will definitely succeed.

115
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:39,660
What do you mean?

116
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:43,260
It sounds like

117
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:45,980
you're doubtful about this.

118
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:47,700
No, I'm praising you.

119
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:55,180
This time,
you're probably having a boy too.

120
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:56,460
I hope so.

121
00:06:57,140 --> 00:06:59,060
Otherwise, my mother-in-law
would give me a hard time.

122
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:03,380
Jiali is back.

123
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:04,380
Mom,

124
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:07,540
I might stay at home for some time.

125
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:10,780
What happened?

126
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,740
I want to start a small business.

127
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:14,980
It's good you want to move back.

128
00:07:14,980 --> 00:07:16,300
I'll tell your Grandma later.

129
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:17,980
She will be very happy.

130
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:20,540
What kind of small business?

131
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:22,940
Old profession: vegetable business.

132
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,340
Isn't that selling vegetables?

133
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:28,500
Yes, selling vegetables.

134
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:30,740
Jiali,

135
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:32,180
I admire you.

136
00:07:33,380 --> 00:07:34,540
Admire what?

137
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:35,960
You can adapt to any situation.

138
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:40,580
Is your foreign trade business so soft?

139
00:07:40,580 --> 00:07:41,540
You needn't go to work?

140
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:44,180
It's more than just soft,
if this continues...

141
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:45,980
I'm afraid I can’t even get wages.

142
00:07:46,180 --> 00:07:47,380
Don't say that.

143
00:07:47,380 --> 00:07:48,860
As long as your unit doesn't lay you off,

144
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:49,780
you should keep working.

145
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,380
Yes, I inherited this work,

146
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:53,780
I have to bear it for a lifetime.

147
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,780
You didn't say this as conditions were good,
but now start complaining?

148
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:58,980
The situation is bad for everyone now.

149
00:07:58,980 --> 00:08:00,700
That's why
a family needs a division of labor.

150
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:03,060
My husband refuses to work outside.

151
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,260
If I also just sit and wait,

152
00:08:05,540 --> 00:08:06,980
we'll have no hope for the future.

153
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,660
Look at our family,

154
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:10,940
Jiali has come out, and her husband is
in the Armed Forces Department.

155
00:08:11,380 --> 00:08:12,940
Although Jiawen and her husband
haven't quit,

156
00:08:12,940 --> 00:08:14,300
her husband is running a business,

157
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:15,580
he might earn big money.

158
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,140
Not to mention Jiayi.

159
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:17,980
She's rich.

160
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:19,900
Jiahuan's husband also came out.

161
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:20,980
He has skills.

162
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,620
Even if just like Hongyu,

163
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:23,660
driving a taxi.

164
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:25,540
This is also a money-making job.

165
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:27,060
As for my husband,

166
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:28,700
he's in a big pit,

167
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:29,900
just sitting at the bottom of a well.

168
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,980
You know, sometimes it's better
to stay still than to move.

169
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,700
Now you have a house,

170
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:35,060
and your job is stable,

171
00:08:35,260 --> 00:08:36,700
you just need to raise a child.

172
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,460
His brother and sister-in-law
can also help,

173
00:08:38,780 --> 00:08:39,860
what more do you want?

174
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:42,900
Jiali, why don't you understand?

175
00:08:42,900 --> 00:08:45,300
You need to keep up with the wave
of reform and opening-up.

176
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:46,780
Now China is like a parking lot,

177
00:08:46,780 --> 00:08:47,990
there are parking spaces everywhere,

178
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:49,060
as long as you occupy one,

179
00:08:49,060 --> 00:08:50,260
this is yours.

180
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:51,700
A parking lot?

181
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,660
Do you even have a car?

182
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:55,980
I have a bicycle.

183
00:08:57,220 --> 00:08:58,900
Does a bicycle need a parking lot?

184
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:00,900
She's a fool.

185
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,220
When I give birth to this child,

186
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:11,900
I have to come back
for postpartum recovery.

187
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:14,020
Hongyu's Mom can't take care of me.

188
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:17,140
She must take care of you.

189
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:19,460
If she doesn't take care of you,

190
00:09:19,770 --> 00:09:21,900
let her pay to find someone
to take care of you.

191
00:09:22,410 --> 00:09:25,040
Mom, you don't care about me at all.

192
00:09:25,820 --> 00:09:27,360
How could I not?

193
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:28,940
You're now heavily pregnant.

194
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:30,940
Stop running back and forth.

195
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:32,140
Stop exhausting yourself.

196
00:09:33,180 --> 00:09:35,140
His mom can't cook well.

197
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:38,020
You're picky.

198
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:39,180
I'm not doing it for myself,

199
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:42,060
but for the sake of our future generations.

200
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:43,340
Jiaxi,

201
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:45,180
as a woman,

202
00:09:45,180 --> 00:09:47,500
you have to go through this.

203
00:09:48,660 --> 00:09:50,100
When the time comes, don't be afraid,

204
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,580
Mom will be with you.

205
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:55,060
You just need to smoothly
bring him into the world,

206
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:56,420
that's all.

207
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,760
- Blow on it.
- Ok. I'll do it.

208
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,400
Alright.

209
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,680
Is it tasty?

210
00:10:18,690 --> 00:10:19,570
Yes, it is.

211
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,200
Is it thick?

212
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,120
A bit.

213
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,600
- A bit thick.
- But it's okay.

214
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:24,920
Alright.

215
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:27,960
Jiaxi.

216
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,040
Continue.

217
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:32,880
No need, I'm full.

218
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,840
Come, let me show you something nice.

219
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,040
Isn't it cute?

220
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,480
Isn't it beautiful?

221
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,320
Yes, it is.

222
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,880
I made it by myself,

223
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,280
stitch by stitch.

224
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:50,960
You're so considerate, Mom.

225
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,440
That's right.

226
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,800
I carefully selected the colors.

227
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,080
This is suitable for boys,

228
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:56,920
right?

229
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,160
- Looks good.
- Mom,

230
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,280
its gender is not certain now.

231
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:05,440
Yes, never mind. It's our child.

232
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,440
- Mom,
- Looks good.

233
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,680
it's getting late.

234
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:11,840
Let's rest.

235
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,680
Pregnant women cannot lack sleep.

236
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,280
It's okay.

237
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,600
Yes, sleep.

238
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,480
Sleep well.

239
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:18,950
Once you are well-rested,

240
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:21,040
our first child will grow up
strong and healthy.

241
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:21,960
Go to sleep.

242
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:23,800
Good night, Mom.

243
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,040
Sleep.

244
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,160
Hurry up.

245
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:36,880
She goes downstairs?

246
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,520
- Yes.
- Come over.

247
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,680
Your Mom did it on purpose.

248
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,480
She meant well.

249
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,600
Do you think so?

250
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,760
She didn't mean well at all.

251
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,520
She just wants to achieve her own goals.

252
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:52,800
How could she make it by herself?

253
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,360
Does she have the skill to make this?

254
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,200
Check it by yourself.

255
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,320
- She bought it?
- Yes.

256
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,120
This little duck is too difficult for her.

257
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,200
Your Mom always lies.

258
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,510
Whether it's bought or woven,
it's the same.

259
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,400
My Mom spent money.

260
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:11,360
Tell me, do you want a boy or a girl?

261
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:15,560
A girl.

262
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:28,620
Feed me.

263
